You can use the [`clickMapObject`](https://www.amcharts.com/docs/v3/reference/ammap/#clickMapObject_event) listener on the map to capture what bubble was clicked. The image itself is stored in the mapObject property of the event:

      &quot;listeners&quot;: [{
        &quot;event&quot;: &quot;clickMapObject&quot;,
        &quot;method&quot;: function(ev) {
          alert(&#39;clicked on &#39; + ev.mapObject.title)
        }
      }]

Note that in order to make the image clickable, you have to set [`selectable`](https://www.amcharts.com/docs/v3/reference/imagessettings/#selectable_property) to `true` in `imagesSettings`:

      &quot;imagesSettings&quot;: {
        &quot;selectable&quot;: true
      }

