If you need a single instance of `IService` that will share between requests, then you can register `IService` as a singleton. 

To do that add this code to Startup.cs

    services.AddSingleton&lt;IService&gt;(s = ServiceFactory.GetAppService());

then, this code to the constructor of `ValuesController`

    public ValuesController(IService service)
    {
        _service = service;
    }

and remove this line

    _service = ServiceFactory.GetAppService();

